eo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-4tV","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":40829,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/08\/28\/rahmah-animals\/","url_meta":{"origin":17231,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Animals: Be merciful even as you slaughter for food","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 28, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Umamah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever is merciful, even as he slaughters his animal, then Allah will be merciful to him on the Day of Resurrection.\u201d Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad lil-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 381 Grade:\u00a0Hasan\u00a0(fair) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0623\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":905,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/07\/06\/umar-mercy-pardon-forgiveness\/","url_meta":{"origin":17231,"position":1},"title":"Umar on Forgiveness: No mercy for the unmerciful, unforgiving","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 6, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Qabisah ibn Jabir reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \"Whoever does not show mercy will not receive mercy. Whoever does not forgive others will not be forgiven. Whoever does not pardon others will not be pardoned. Whoever does not protect others will not be protected.\"\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":42690,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/03\/07\/prophet-most-merciful-dependents\/","url_meta":{"origin":17231,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Family: The Prophet is most merciful to his dependents","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 7, 2025","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, was the most merciful of people to his dependents. He had his son suckled in part of Madina, and the husband of his wet-nurse was a blacksmith. We used to go to him and the house would be\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":22096,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/02\/27\/rahmah-sheep-slaughter\/","url_meta":{"origin":17231,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Mercy: Have mercy on the sheep, do not slaughter","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 27, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Qurra ibn Iyas reported: A man said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, I would have slaughtered a sheep but I had mercy on it.\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIf you had mercy on the sheep, Allah will have mercy on you twice.\u201d Source: al-Adab\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":29330,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/13\/sahabah-said-when-praised\/","url_meta":{"origin":17231,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Humility: What the companions said when praised","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 13, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Adi ibn Artah reported: When a man among the companions of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, was praised for his righteousness, he would say, \u201cO Allah, do not blame me for what they say and forgive me for what they do not know!\u201d Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad lil-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37225,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/10\/25\/ibn-masud-on-fahishah\/","url_meta":{"origin":17231,"position":5},"title":"Ibn Mas\u2019ud on Akhlaq: Vulgarity worst character trait of a believer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 25, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu al-Ahwas reported: Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cThe most blameworthy characteristic in a believer is obscenity.\u201d Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad 314 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0648\u064e\u0635\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0646 \u0645\u0633\u0639\u0648\u062f \u0631\u0636\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u0646\u0647 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0645\u064f \u0623\u064e\u062e\u0652\u0644\u064e\u0627\u0642\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064f\u0624\u0652\u0645\u0650\u06